"begin": 654, "end": 659}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7422"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "cardiac VEGF-A mRNA", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9217172861099243, "span": {"begin": 723, "end": 742}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chicks", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.47709012031555176, "span": {"begin": 822, "end": 828}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "AHR", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9887664914131165, "span": {"begin": 843, "end": 846}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3091"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "HIF1&alpha", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8718786239624023, "span": {"begin": 879, "end": 889}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:405"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ARNT", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9778180122375488, "span": {"begin": 895, "end": 899}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7422"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "VEGF-A", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9950152039527893, "span": {"begin": 943, "end": 949}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7422"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "VEGF-A", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9284186363220215, "span": {"begin": 1041, "end": 1047}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9031"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chick", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.8129538297653198, "span": {"begin": 1062, "end": 1067}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7422"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "VEGF-A", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9952172040939331, "span": {"begin": 1096, "end": 1102}}], "text": "Include consideration of temporal concordance here     In chick embryo development, the oxygen gradient within myocardium induces VEGF mRNA in cardiac myocytes (Cheung 1997).  ARNT- and HIF-1&alpha;- null mice cannot survive gestation due to defects in vasculature development (Iyer et al. 1998; Maltepe et al. 1997)  Hypoxia increased VEGF expression in AHR+/+ aortic endothelial cells (MAECs) but not in AHR-/- MAECs, suggesting that HIF-1&alpha; modulates endothelial VEGF expression in an AHR-dependent manner (Roman et al. 2009)  HIF-1&alpha; protein degradation by 2-methoxyestradio blocked hypoxia induced VEGF expression in AHR+/+ but not AHR-/- MAECs (Roman et al. 2009)  Exogenous hypoxia significantly increased cardiac VEGF-A mRNA expression and expanded its spatial expression in the myocardium of developing chicks; in contrast, AHR activation (which competes with HIF1&alpha; for ARNT) tended to limit the spatial expression of VEGF-A to ventricular trabeculae (Ivnitski-Steele et al. 2004)  AHR activation reduced myocardial VEGF-A expression in chick embryos and reduced explant VEGF-A secretion (Ivnitski-Steele et al. 2005)   &nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:53:50 +0000 2026"}